"""Auto-generated by scripts/sdk-facades.ts. Do not edit.

Proxmox VE WebSocket helpers.

Two console flows share the same two-step pipeline:

    1. POST {prefix}/{termproxy|vncproxy|vncshell} → ticket + port
    2. GET  {prefix}/vncwebsocket?port=…&vncticket=…  → HTTP 101 Upgrade

Framing on the upgraded socket differs by parent POST:
    - termproxy → text framing (``0:LEN:MSG``, ``1:COLS:ROWS:``, ``2`` ping)
    - vncproxy / vncshell → raw binary RFB

Architecture (SOLID):

    - :class:`TicketIssuer` (Strategy) — one impl per (flow × resource)
      combo; adding a new console flow is one new class with no edits
      to the dispatcher (Open/Closed).
    - :class:`FrameCodec` (Strategy) — text vs binary framing.
    - :class:`AuthAttacher` (Strategy) — composes Cookie / API-token.
    - :class:`WebSocketTransport` (Adapter) — wraps the optional
      ``websocket-client`` package so the rest depends only on an
      abstraction (DIP).
    - :class:`ConsoleConnector` (Template Method) — orchestrates the
      pipeline; concrete connectors plug in their strategies.
    - :class:`TerminalSession` / :class:`VncSession` — delegate framing
      to a codec; they don't know about the wire format.

Synchronous design — matches the rest of the generated SDK. Backed by
the optional ``websocket-client`` package (``pip install
websocket-client``).
"""

